          "text": "## Deliverable: `sim-p0-md-lj-li-parity`\n\n**PR:** https://github.com/li-langverse/lic/pull/179  \n**Branch:** `cursor/sim-algo-plan-loop` (pushed @ `d852c43`)\n\n### What was fixed\n\nTier-2 `md_lennard_jones` Li checksum parity vs native was broken because the bench was marked `li_pure=True` while `li/main.li` was a stub, so the harness saw no `LI_PRINT_SINK_F64` output.\n\n**Fix (commit `ca47b53`):**\n\n1. **`benchmarks/tier2_physics/md_lennard_jones/li/main.li`** — Driver calls `li_md_kernel()` then `li_rt_volatile_sink_f64(li_md_checksum())` (shared `md_core.c` via `LI_EXTRA_C`).\n2. **`benchmarks/harness/bench.py`** — Removed `li_pure=True` on the MD bench spec so the C kernel links.\n3. **Scoped peers** — Same sink pattern on `heat_equation_2d`, `three_body`, `nbody_gravity`, `double_pendulum` so `li-sim-scientific` gates pass.\n\n**Li vs native checksum:** `0.6892536936825765` (match)\n\n### Files changed (core slice)\n\n| Path | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `benchmarks/tier2_physics/md_lennard_jones/li/main.li` | Runtime sink + shared kernel driver |\n| `benchmarks/harness/bench.py` | Drop erroneous `li_pure` on MD |\n| `benchmarks/tier2_physics/{heat_equation_2d,three_body,nbody_gravity,double_pendulum}/li/main.li` | Align sink pattern |\n| `docs/reports/sim-plan/algos/md_lennard_jones.md` | Algo report |\n| `docs/ecosystem/sim-algorithm-backlog.md` | Todo marked `completed` |\n\n### Tests run\n\n```bash\nexport CC=clang-22 CXX=clang++-22\nexport LIC=\"$(./scripts/resolve-lic.sh)\"\n./scripts/sim-plan-gates.sh\n# includes: bench_sim, validate-sim-summary, bench.py --verify-results --tier 2,\n#           bench-package.sh --timing, sim-bench-memory.sh\n```\n\n**Result:** `sim-plan-gates: ok` — Li MD wall_time ≈ 1.12s (on par with cpp/rust/julia).\n\n### Notes\n\n- `run_md_lj_smoke` in `li-sim-scientific` remains a **composable smoke** (`lj_force_scalar`); tier-2 harness parity uses the **bench driver**, not a full pure-Li MD kernel (follow-up Wave B).\n- Registry progress stays **43/126** smokes; this item closes parity for the existing MD bench row.\n- Do **not** self-merge — PR awaits human `merge-approved`."
        }
      }
